{"questionId":"11821","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question will investigate the solution to a coupled system of differential equations and how to transform it to a system that can be solved by the eigenvector method.</p>\n<p>It is desired to solve the coupled system of differential equations</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot x = x + 2y - 50\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>50</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot y = 2x + y - 40\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>40</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;represent the population of two types of symbiotic coral and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is time measured in decades.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show how using the substitution <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X = x - 10{\\text{,}}\\,\\,Y = y - 20\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>Y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>20</mn>\n</math></span> transforms the system of differential equations into <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {\\dot X = X + 2Y} \\\\   {\\dot Y = 2X + Y}  \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mover>\n              <mi>X</mi>\n              <mo>˙</mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>Y</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mover>\n              <mi>Y</mi>\n              <mo>˙</mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>Y</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X = x - 10{\\text{,}}\\,\\,Y = y - 20 \\Rightarrow \\dot X = \\dot x{\\text{,}}\\,\\,\\dot Y = \\dot y\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>10</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>Y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>20</mn>\n  <mo stretchy=\"false\">⇒</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>X</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>Y</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {\\dot X = \\left( {X + 10} \\right) + 2\\left( {Y + 20} \\right) - 50 = X + 2Y} \\\\   {\\dot Y = 2\\left( {X + 10} \\right) + \\left( {Y + 20} \\right) - 40 = 2X + Y}  \\end{array}\">\n  <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mover>\n              <mi>X</mi>\n              <mo>˙</mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>X</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>Y</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>20</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>50</mn>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>Y</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n    <mtr>\n      <mtd>\n        <mrow>\n          <mrow>\n            <mover>\n              <mi>Y</mi>\n              <mo>˙</mo>\n            </mover>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>X</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>10</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mrow>\n            <mo>(</mo>\n            <mrow>\n              <mi>Y</mi>\n              <mo>+</mo>\n              <mn>20</mn>\n            </mrow>\n            <mo>)</mo>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>−</mo>\n          <mn>40</mn>\n          <mo>=</mo>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n          <mi>X</mi>\n          <mo>+</mo>\n          <mi>Y</mi>\n        </mrow>\n      </mtd>\n    </mtr>\n  </mtable>\n</math></span>&nbsp;<em><strong>&nbsp; &nbsp; M1A1AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11821","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.3d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Show how using the substitution X = x − 10 , Y = y − 20 transforms the system of differential equations into X ˙ = X + 2 Y Y ˙ = 2 X + Y .","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}